### Service 3: Users ###

### Register a new user
POST http://localhost:3003/api/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Login (Get Token)
# @name login
POST http://localhost:3003/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Variable for Token
@authToken = {{login.response.body.token}}


### Service 1: Books ###

### Get all books
GET http://localhost:3001/api/books

### Add a new book (Requires Auth)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/books
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "The Great Gatsby",
  "author": "F. Scott Fitzgerald",
  "year": 1925
}

### Get specific book
GET http://localhost:3001/api/books/1

### Delete book (Requires Auth)
DELETE http://localhost:3001/api/books/1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}


### Service 2: Orders ###

### Create Order (Requires Auth)
# Note: Ensure a book exists with ID used here.
POST http://localhost:3002/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "userId": 1,
  "bookId": 1,
  "quantity": 2
}

### Get Orders for generic user
GET http://localhost:3002/api/orders/1

### Update Order (Requires Auth)
PATCH http://localhost:3002/api/orders/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "quantity": 5
}

### Delete Order (Requires Auth)
DELETE http://localhost:3002/api/orders/1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
